Defendant Kerry L. Stevenson in court with Attorney Steven R. Kohn.  Defendant Kerry L. Stevenson in custody.  Bruce Poquette appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Victim's mother Patti Price to listen by phone.  DA Poquette makes statement asks for maximum sentence.  DA Poquette gives letter to court from Hayward Memorial Hospital already given to defense.   Court asks victims to be brief and come forward and tell court why Mr. Stevenson should be sentenced in a particular way.  First the Court asks if Patricia Price, Claudia Bunny's mother, would like to speak.  Ms. Price makes statement.  Emily Bunny makes statement.  Claudia's sister Ellen Johnson makes statement  on behalf of herself and 2 other sisters (Maureen Lapham and Diane Doody)  Maria Alesse Claudia's friend makes statement.  Lisa Phillips, friend of Claudia, makes statement.  Amy Rizzo, friend of Claudia, makes statement.  Lori Dobrowolski, childhood friend, makes statement.  Kristin Kennedy, childhood friend, makes statement.  Wendy Bodnar, friend of Claudia, makes statement.  Tom Maertin makes statement and reads letter from Claudia's nephew - Sean Bunny.   Dan Bunny makes statement.  Mr. Kohn makes statement goes over restitution points.  District Attorney Bruce Poquette, Attorney Kohn had a conference, off record in chambers, regarding the restitution.  Now Mr. Kohn asks for those who wish to speak regarding  Mr. Stevenson.  Court asks again for brief statements.  Chloe Boullion,  defendant's mother, makes statement.  Tammy Hemby, Kerry ex-wife, makes statement.  Jessica Stevenson, Kerry's daughter, makes statement.  Defendant's Attorney, Mr. Kohn makes statement.  Attorney Kohn reads letter.  Defendant Kerry L. Stevenson makes statement.  

